block stylesblock
    link(rel='stylesheet', href="/stylesheets/LayoutTests.css")
    
style.
    h2 {
        color: chocolate;
    }
style.img.   
    transparent {
        zoom: 1;
        filter: alpha(opacity=50);
        opacity: 0.5;
    }
    
block append content
    
div(style="height:auto;width:100%; overflow: auto")
    h2(align="center")
        | MashOver Web Site Simulator
    h3( align="center", style="color: chocolate")
        | Selecting a map type from the tabs above will simulate a web site in this container.
    div(style="border:2px solid green; margin: 8px")
        h4  Depending on the tab selected, the web site will host a Google Map, Open Source map, or ArcGIS Online map.
        
        span
            p 
                | The Collapse/Expand button 
                img(ng-src="../stylesheets/images/{{sumExpandCollapse}}.png", width="2%" height="2%")
                | at the top will open or close the web site selection tabs container above.
    
    div(style="border:2px solid green; margin: 8px")
        p After selecting a map type, it will appear on the left of the screen.  An accordion container on the right side will display some other web site verbage.  The container also contains instructions on how to use the system.  Finally, it contains expandable panels that allow the user to search ArcGIS Online for interesting map layers and map groups.
    
        p After a search is conducted, selecting a map layer will display dialogs for directing the new layer to the same window, a new window, or a new tab.  It will also prompt for a channel name to allow all opened maps to synchronize over web sockets.







